deck: A circus snake charmer with a secret.
description:
60 years ago and young girl was kidnapped by a cult and caged with the snakes. Then something happened to the girl and she gained powers. She managed to get free from the cage and killed her captors. Then she met a demon.

Years later joined the World's End Circus, where she fit in with the other freaks. She used her psychic talent only when needed. She lied about her past and told she was a circus snake charmer.

Ophidia was kidnapped again by the cult and offered as a food for Sargoth. After the demon was summoned, Ophidia revealed her abilities, by transforming into a half-snake herself and charmed the snake-god Sargoth. She made him kill all the cult members and released the other prisoners. She then sent Sargoth back to where he came.
name: Ophidia

deck: Kowl is a fictional character in the Masters of the Universe franchise, specifically appearing in the series She-Ra: Princess of Power (cartoon).
description:
Kowl is depicted as a small flying creature capable of speaking. His wings are not unlike large ears, and he has the overall appearance of something akin to an Owl mixed with a Koala, hence his name. It is mentioned that there aren't many members of his species left, and most of his relatives are dead.

Kowl is colored light tan/brown, with yellow eyes, a grey beak, and a rainbow-esque pattern on the inside of his ears.

He is something of an acerbic, sarcastic character who is a constant companion of the members of the Great Rebellion. Kowl tends to serve as comic relief as he is often cracking jokes and making slightly rude, piercing observations about the events unfolding around him.

Kowl is one of only four Etherians who is aware that Adora and She-Ra are the same individual.

All of her people possess bee-like wings on the backs which give them the ability to fly. Sweetbee is sent by The Hive to scout for a new planet to colonise, to find out if the planet has a good source of water and also if the people of the planet are peaceful in nature.

deck: High priest of the Cult of Chaos.
description:
Origin

Willam Baxter was a normal, nice guy. Married, had a daughter named Emma, and worked as an air traffic controller. All that changed when he found a book in an antiquarian book store. This book, The Crimson Chronicles, wqas written by an occultist named Ethan Shroud. He became fixated with it, locking himself up for days in his study, reading it over and over. He stopped bathing, chaving, eating, going to work. He sought out the Cult of Chaos in real life. When he finally found them, they bowed before him and said he was the reincarnation of their high priest. William started calling himself Ethan Shroud and left his family.

deck: Perfuma is a ditzy but cute and very pretty blonde member of the Rebellion.
description:
Unlike the other members of the Rebellion, she does not appear to be afraid of Hordak and the other Hordesmen. On one occasion she is captured by Hordak and imprisoned in a dungeon in the Fright Zone. While a prisoner in the Fright Zone, Perfuma decides that it can benefit from a bit of sprucing up. So she escapes and goes around the Fright Zone decorating it with flowers wherever she goes. Hordak is so incensed by this that he begs She-Ra to take her back into the Rebellion.

Being an ecomancer, she has total control over plants, allowing her to create vines, trees and vast fields of flora at will without the need of sunlight to maintain her plants. Her powers also have been shown to nullify/transform dark energy and fire into cascades of flowers; probably the reason she doesn't fear Hordak.
name: Perfuma

volume_credits.name: Masters of the Universe/Princess of Power: Twins of Power

deck: A powerful magically enchanted spirit.
description:
Light Hope resided within the Crystal Castle that was situated on top of the mountain Skydancer on the planet Etheria. This ancient being served the forces of good and was privy to secrets from the times of the First Ones who were the founders of Etheria. During its time as the keeper of the Crystal Castle, Light Hope met with Agho; King of the Trolls who had journeyed to find it. During their time together, Light Hope asked Agho to keep the location of the Crystal Castle a secret to which the Troll King gave his word.

In later years, Castle Bright Moon faced a terrible attack from the Evil Horde leading to She-Ra going on a quest to find the Crystal Castle. Through a riddle given by Agho, she managed to find the Castle and Light Hope allowed her entry whilst stating that it had long awaited her arrival. Manifesting itself as a colossal pillar of light and told her of one way to save Bright Moon from Shadow Weaver's attack. Namely the Great Clock at the center of Etheria which could speed up time to allow the moons to move past the eclipse and fill Queen Angellawith their power.

Light Hope was responsible for transporting She-Ra to Etheria's center but not before warning her of the protectors of the Great Clock. Once there, she managed to succeed in her quest which in turn defeated the Horde's planned destruction of Castle Bright Moon. Afterwards, She-Ra met with Light Hope who asked her to also keep the location of the Crystal Castle a secret. Furthermore, it asked her to treat the Castle as her haven and that She-Ra should visit it more often to which she agreed thus leading to her becoming the defender of the Crystal Castle.
name: Light Hope

volume_credits.name: Masters of the Universe/Princess of Power: Twins of Power

deck: Scorpia is a fictional character in the animated television series She-Ra: Princess of Power and in the comics series She-Ra.
description:
Scorpia was the warrior queen of Scorpioni people, race of warriors mutant half scorpions, his kingdom was at war with the mighty God "Shatalak" (creator of Scorpioni people) and King of the enemy who came from the fifth dimension to defeat the "Scorpion King" father of Scorpia who had died, his kingdom was taken by Shatalak who wanted to dominate all Etheria, Hordak and his troops under the command of captain Adora fought a battle with Shatalak who defeated God, destroying the gate of the fifth dimension completely losing his powers and sent to prison in the world of the horde.

The Scorpioni kingdom became a dark desert leaving the ruin of his castle where Scorpia lives in next to Crimson Waste, she surrenders to the world of the horde as a thank you, a part of the team as troop lieutenant.

At this place she owns slaves, which suggest that she is a powerful figure on Etheria. with your castle scorpion. Within the home can be seen a throne, suggesting Scorpia has some kind of rule over a new region of Etheria.

Scorpia and Catra possess a fierce rivalry between them, only working together as a last resort. She possesses claw-like pincers instead of hands and a powerful tail which she can employ to capture members of the Rebellion. Her tail is at times a disadvantage to her as She-Ra uses it several times to hurl her out of the way. She is not the most intelligent member of the Horde and is easily fooled, which is evidenced on several occasions, most notably when she allows Bow to enter the secret factory of the Horde believing him to be a handsome inspector.

deck: Flutterina is a member of the Great Rebellion, in the planet Etheria.
description:
Before becoming a freedom fighter, Flutterina was a cute slave girl from the land of Sand Valley on Etheria. After She-Ra brought her to the Crystal Castle, the girl previously known only as Small One was transformed into Flutterina via a magical cocoon.

Flutterina could hover and fly, and possessed large beautiful butterfly wings that were powerful enough to disperse enemies when she beat them at full power. In dire straits, she could transform her entire body into a butterfly to escape the Evil Horde; she could also control butterflies of all kinds, using them as messengers and spies.
